    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIt could be a possible regresssion, for `vim.highlight.range` can not highlight the whole line. Tried with regtype = V or regtype = l, as mentioned in setreg.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim -U none\r\n\r\npopulate the file with at least one line, changing inclusive makes no difference\r\n\r\n    :lua vim.highlight.range(0, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"user\"), \"IncSearch\", { 0, 0 }, { 0, -1 }, { regtype = \"V\", inclusive = false | true })\r\n\r\npopulate the file with a few lines, that works, highlights linewise, between the lines\r\n\r\n    :lua vim.highlight.range(0, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"user\"), \"IncSearch\", { 0, 0 }, { 1, -1 }, { regtype = \"V\", inclusive = false | true })\r\n\r\nNote that the highlight works in case the end range is on a different line instead, i.e the row is not the same as in the start opts.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe entire line in the buffer should be highlighted.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.10.0\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nubuntu 22\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nalacritty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\ngithub",
